item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
WALKID

Walking School Bus Volunteering Aid


Walkid wants to spread the message of hope and compassion.

We believe that a single action can make a difference in the community,
and that collective action can greatly impact the world

What is Walking school bus(WSB) program?

How to become a WSB volunteer?

Where are WSB councils and schools?

How to work with children?



THE WALKING SCHOOL BUS PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School bus (WSB) Program is a pioneering way of walking primary school children to and from the school with volunteers along a safely audited route. It is a school bus powered by legs and not by an engine. School going kids walk to school in a group with Volunteers as ‘Driver’ and ‘Conductor’. The bus stops at pre-determined stops to pick up children along the way from their home, and vice versa for the way to school. There are around 70 Councils in Victoria who have adopted the WSB program.

WSB Volunteer

WSB volunteers are adults who engage in the WSB Program to walk children to and from the school along with a predetermined safe route.

WSB Benefits

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. Children can get to school safely and on time.
2. Children get regular physical activity and exercise, gain a sense of independence.
3. It provides a safer, non-polluting, and sustainable transport alternative.
4. Reduces time pressure for parents as they don’t have to accompany their children to school every day.
5. Reduces the number of vehicles subsequently eases traffic congestion around the school zones.

DID YOU KNOW？

Only ONE in FOUR Australian children walk to school due to lack of adult supervision and safety concerns. Together we can make a difference. Create a safer school route by engaging in the Walking School Bus Program.

1 Number of schools engaged in the WSB Program  1 Number of volunteers in the WSB program 1 Number of councils in the WSB Programs

We need more Walking School Bus Volunteers

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

Volunteering for a few hours can make a difference in society. Start your WSB volunteering journey today.

FIVE STEPS TO START YOUR WSB VOLUNTEERING JOURNEY

1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation
  • All Councils require volunteers a Police check and a Working with Children’s Check
  • Refer to Checklist to see what you need
3. Find your council based on your preferred location
  • Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.
4. Contact with the Council

  • You can contact the council for inquiries with your WSB volunteering journey.

5. Submit your WSB Volunteer Application
  • When you are ready with all the required documents and requirements, you can submit your application. Most councils use email for the application process.

FIND WSB COUNCILS AND SCHOOLS NEAR YOU

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Input your preferred location on the Enter your location block.

CLICK ON the Hamburger button 三

Choose Councils to find councils else choose Schools to find Schools.

Select Radius

Select the preferred radius (1 km to 300 km) to find the nearest councils and schools within that radius based on your location.

Select the WSB council and schools

Choose your preferred WSB councils and schools on the map

Direction

Click on ‘Get Directions’ to get routes to the preferred council and schools from your location.

Tips for WSB volunteers

https://youtu.be/1xVXOPfwEiI

[interact id="5e9bee1cb789c100146c61c1" type="quiz"]


Who are we?

We are Tech Warriors with a Team of four Postgraduate students from Monash University. We are a peculiar bunch of very different people across the globe. One common belief we all share is to create a safer environment and make a difference in the community.

MELBOURNE WSB PROGRAM

If you're having fun to help students to school safely Become a WSB Program's Volunteer

the walking school bus

WSB Program

A Walking School Bus is a school bus powered not by an engine but by legs. Children walk in a group to school, with an adult 'driver' in the front and an adult 'conductor' at the rear.

The WSB Program have many benefits for children and school. If you want to know more click here

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

Having fun to help students to school safely? Become a WSB Program's Volunteer!



THE WALKING SCHOOL PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School Bus Program refer to the school, local council, and the volunteers of the WSB create a walking school bus which powered by legs, Volunteers like a driver to lead students group walking to school, and Volunteers as 'driver' in the front and rear. There is almost 70 local council engaged in the WSB Program in the VIC, AU.  Many ‘buses’ have become a very positive part of school and community life. 

WSB Volunteer

The WSB volunteer indicates the adults who engage in the WSB Program. They may come from different industries or they own different cultures. They all focus to help students go to school safely.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. The WSB program help students get to school safely.
2. The students can learn knowledge about traffic safety.
3. The students can get more regular physical activities that benefit their health.

WE NEED MORE VOLUNTEER

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

This website aims to encourage people to engage in WSB Program and Provide instruction for guiding people to be a volunteer.

Status of Volunteer

1 Accidents in School Zone

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text. 

1 Existing Volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text. 

1 Shortage of volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text. 

FIVE STEPS TO BECOME A WSB VOLUNTEER

Most frequent questions and answers
1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation

All Councils  require volunteers a Police Check. The volunteers who work with children need a Working with Children’s Check

3. Select a Council you prefer in our Council Recommendation

Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.

4. Contact with the Council

You can contact with the council to consult whether they have any specific requirements.

5. Submit your Application

When you prepare all the material and requirements from the council, You can submit you application. Most councils use email to receive the material. Here, you should  note that you are interesting in WSB program

FIND WSB COUNCIL NEARBY YOU

Our gallery

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Please input your address on the right location box.

Select Radius

Select the distance, which decide a recommendation arrange that centers on you

Select your prefer COUNCIL

Select an council you like on the right map

Derection

Click the get direction, this provide a route recommendation from your location to the council you selected

item.title: WSB User Journey
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
What does a Walking School Bus Volunteer Day Look Like?

Stay in - We win

Before You Start

Explore

During the Journey

Explore

Safety Procedures

Explore

Emergency Procedures

Explore

Before You Start

  • Plan your route well in advance by using our Journey Planner
  • Check if there are any road closures in your preferred route
  • Carry the Walking School bus Backpack
  • Follow the identified walking route and use designated crossing points to cross the roads.
Back

Instruction

Input your starting location as A and destination as B 

Choose mode of transport

Drag and select your choice of route depending on Traffic congestion

Or Refer to the Video for more details

http://www.wsbvolunteer.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/My-Movie.mp4

Legend

Traffic congestion indicated in red, yellow and green

Red - Highly Congested

Yellow - Medium congested

Green - No congestion

 

Pointer on the generated route used to drag and select route

[wp_mapbox_gl_js map_id="919"]

During the Journey​

  • Ensure that kids do not run
  • Maintain a daily attendance sheet of the bus route
  • Maintain regular monitoring practices
  • Ensure that kids are not carrying skateboards, scooters, rollerblades or bicycles 
  • Follow the Safety Procedure guidelines to avoid accidents
  • Follow the Emergency Procedure guidelines in case of any accidents.
Back

Safety Procedures

  • Road crossings should be made as a group. 
  • The ‘bus driver’ volunteer should wait at the corner for all the participants to catch up.
  • Look out for and advise the group on potential dangers or footpath obstructions.
  • The volunteers should encourage the children to “Stop, Look, Listen and Think” while crossing
Back

Emergency Procedures

Minor Accidents:

  1. Please assess the injury
  2. Reassure the child 
  3. Use the tissues, gloves, napkins available in the Backpack
  4. Continue with your journey if everything is fine
  5. Report the injury to the school or parent at the end of the bus route

Major Accidents:

  1. Please contact emergency services (000), the child’s parent, and the school and wait for assistance to arrive. 
  2. An incident report should be submitted to the school and the Walking School Bus Project Officer. 
  3. Use the emergency contact numbers list provided inside the backpack.
Back

ACCIDENT STATISTICS

1 Average Number of Children with Road Accident Injuries in Victoria in 5 years 0 Average Number of Children who lost their lives in a Road Accident in Victoria in 5 years

Road Accident Deaths - Victorian Children

The bar chart represents the number of children who lost their lives due to Road Accidents in Victoria from the year 2011 to 2019.

Using this historical data, the chart represents an estimate of the number of deaths in the next 5 years i.e from 2020 to 2025.

Road Accidents In Victoria - Hourly basis

The bar chart clearly indicates that many road accidents occur around 8 AM and between 3 PM and 5 PM. 

Most parents prefer driving to drop or pick up their kids from school which leads to traffic congestion and in turn resulting in a crash as parents are under time-pressure.

Accident prone areas in Victoria

The chart represents the Top Five Accident prone areas in Victoria from the year 2013 to 2017.

item.title: FAQ
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
FAQ

What is a Walking School Bus?

The bus travels along a set route to or from school, picking up or dropping off children along the way at designated ‘bus Station’. Bus stops can be meeting points along the route or each child’s front gate.

What kind of work am I supposed to do in the WSB Program?

The WSB Volunteers’ work is picking up children from each “walking bus station” and take them to school safely. You can get the details in WSB User Journey Page.

How many children in a “Walking Bus”?

There are commonly 8 children in a “Walking Bus”, The maximum size of “Walking Bus” is 8 children for every adult on each bus.

How many volunteers work in one Walking school bus ?

The WSB program require two volunteers working together in activity, one is start one is end. Commonly.

What should I do if some children do not arrive “walking bus station” on time?

Sometimes, you can choose to wait for 2 or 3 minutes and contact their parents.  Please make sure you can arrive “next station” on time.

What should I do if children refuse to participate in the morning?

Participation is entirely voluntary. If children do not want to participate, you can try to encourage them or communicate with their parents, that day their parents would take their children to school.

item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
CHECKLIST FOR VOLUNTEERS

[checklist_in_post]

  • National Police Certificate
  • CrimeCheck
  • Working with children check
  • Proof of personal identity e.g. Identity card, Passport or driving license
  • Proof of professional qualifications
  • History of working with children (Optional if no)
  • Reference check (Optional)
  • Schedule of availability (Optional)

[/checklist_in_post]

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: User1
item.content:encoded:
WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

Having fun to help students to school safely? Become a WSB Program's Volunteer!



THE WALKING SCHOOL PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School Bus Program refer to the school, local council, and the volunteers of the WSB create a walking school bus which powered by legs, Volunteers like a driver to lead students group walking to school, and Volunteers as 'driver' in the front and rear. There is almost 70 local council engaged in the WSB Program in the VIC, AU.  Many ‘buses’ have become a very positive part of school and community life. 

WSB Volunteer

The WSB volunteer indicates the adults who engage in the WSB Program. They may come from different industries or they own different cultures. They all focus to help students go to school safely.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. The WSB program help students get to school safely.
2. The students can learn knowledge about traffic safety.
3. The students can get more regular physical activities that benefit their health.

WE NEED MORE VOLUNTEER

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

This website aims to encourage people to engage in WSB Program and Provide instruction for guiding people to be a volunteer.

Status of Volunteer

1 Accidents in School Zone

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text. 

1 Existing Volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text. 

1 Shortage of volunteer

I am text block. Click edit button to change this text. 

FIVE STEPS TO BECOME A WSB VOLUNTEER

Most frequent questions and answers
1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation

All Councils  require volunteers a Police Check. The volunteers who work with children need a Working with Children’s Check

3. Select a Council you prefer in our Council Recommendation

Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.

4. Contact with the Council

You can contact with the council to consult whether they have any specific requirements.

5. Submit your Application

When you prepare all the material and requirements from the council, You can submit you application. Most councils use email to receive the material. Here, you should  note that you are interesting in WSB program

FIND WSB COUNCIL NEARBY YOU

Our gallery

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Please input your address on the right location box.

Select Radius

Select the distance, which decide a recommendation arrange that centers on you

Select your prefer COUNCIL

Select an council you like on the right map

Derection

Click the get direction, this provide a route recommendation from your location to the council you selected

INTERACTIVE LESSON

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
WALKING SCHOOL BUS VOLUNTEER SUPPORT

Get Started

What is the walking school bus program

Where you can engage walking school bus program

How to be a volunteer of walking school bus program

hOW DID YOU WORK WITH CHILD



THE WALKING SCHOOL PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School bus (WSB) Program is a pioneering way of walking primary school children to and from the school with volunteers along a safely audited route. It is a school bus powered by legs and not by an engine. School going kids walk to school in a group with Volunteers as ‘Driver’ and ‘Conductor’. The bus stops at pre-determined stops to pick up children along the way from their home, and vice versa for the way to school. There are around 70 Councils in Victoria who have adopted the WSB program.

WSB Volunteer

WSB volunteers are adults who engage in the WSB Program to walk children to and from the school along with a predetermined safe route.

WSB Benifit

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. Children can get to school safely and on time.
2. Children get regular physical activity and exercise, gain a sense of independence.
3. It provides a safer, non-polluting, and sustainable transport alternative.
4. Reduces time pressure for parents as they don’t have to accompany their children to school every day.
5. Reduces the number of vehicles subsequently eases traffic congestion around the school zones.

WE NEED MORE VOLUNTEERS

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

Volunteering for a few hours can make a difference in society. Start your WSB volunteering journey today

FIVE STEPS TO START YOUR WSB VOLUNTEERING JOURNEY

1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation
  • All Councils require volunteers a Police check and a Working with Children’s Check
3. IT Find your council based on your preferred location
  • Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.
4. Contact with the Council
  • You can contact with the council to consult whether they have any specific requirements.
5. Submit your WSB Volunteer Application
  • When you are ready with all the required documents and requirements from the council, you can submit with your volunteering application. Most councils use email for the application process.

FIND WSB COUNCIL NEARBY YOU

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Input your preferred location on the ‘Enter your location’ block.

Select Radius

Select the preferred radius (1 km to 300 km) to find the nearest councils within that radius based on your location.

COUNCIL SHOULD BE PREFERRED

Select an council you like on the right map

Direction

Click the get direction, this provides a route recommendation from your location to the council you selected

How to work with kids?

item.title: WSB VOLUNTEER SUPPORT
item.dc:creator: user
item.content:encoded:
WALKID

Walking School Bus Volunteering Aid


Walkid wants to spread the message of hope and compassion.

We believe that a single action can make a difference in the community,
and that collective action can greatly impact the world

What is Walking school bus(WSB) program?

How to become a WSB volunteer?

Where are WSB councils and schools?

How to work with children?



THE WALKING SCHOOL BUS PROGRAM

WSB Program

The Walking School bus (WSB) Program is a pioneering way of walking primary school children to and from the school with volunteers along a safely audited route. It is a school bus powered by legs and not by an engine. School going kids walk to school in a group with Volunteers as ‘Driver’ and ‘Conductor’. The bus stops at pre-determined stops to pick up children along the way from their home, and vice versa for the way to school. There are around 70 Councils in Victoria who have adopted the WSB program.

WSB Volunteer

WSB volunteers are adults who engage in the WSB Program to walk children to and from the school along with a predetermined safe route.

WSB Benefits

The WSB Program has many benefits for students and schools. there are five mean benefits of WSB.
1. Children can get to school safely and on time.
2. Children get regular physical activity and exercise, gain a sense of independence.
3. It provides a safer, non-polluting, and sustainable transport alternative.
4. Reduces time pressure for parents as they don’t have to accompany their children to school every day.
5. Reduces the number of vehicles subsequently eases traffic congestion around the school zones.

DID YOU KNOW？

Only ONE in FOUR Australian children walk to school due to lack of adult supervision and safety concerns. Together we can make a difference. Create a safer school route by engaging in the Walking School Bus Program.

1 Number of schools engaged in the WSB Program  1 Number of volunteers in the WSB program 1 Number of council in the WSB Programs

We need more ‘WSB’ Volunteers

The volunteer plays an important role in the WSB Program. However, many local councils face a shortage of volunteers. Therefore, the WSB program needs more volunteers.

Volunteering for a few hours can make a difference in society. Start your WSB volunteering journey today.

FIVE STEPS TO START YOUR WSB VOLUNTEERING JOURNEY

1. What to consider before application
  • The amount of time you can comfortably commit.
  • What skills you can offer.
  • The satisfaction that you would get from the volunteer role.
  • The amount of responsibility you are comfortable with.
2. The material preparation
  • All Councils require volunteers a Police check and a Working with Children’s Check
  • Refer to Checklist to see what you need
3. Find your council based on your preferred location
  • Select a council you like in our Council Recommendation.
4. Contact with the Council

  • You can contact the council for inquiries with your WSB volunteering journey.

5. Submit your WSB Volunteer Application
  • When you are ready with all the required documents and requirements, you can submit your application. Most councils use email for the application process.

Checklist for Volunteers in Vic

[checklist_in_post]

  • National Police Certificate
  • CrimCheck
  • Working with children check
  • Proof of personal identity e.g. Identity card, Passport or driving license
  • Proof of professional qualifications
  • History of working with children (Optional if no)
  • Reference check (Optional)
  • Schedule of availability (Optional)

[/checklist_in_post]

FIND WSB COUNCILS AND SCHOOLS NEAR YOU

INPUT YOUR ADDRESS

Input your preferred location on the ‘Enter your location’ block.

Select Radius

Select the preferred radius (1 km to 300 km) to find the nearest councils within that radius based on your location.

Select the WSB council

Choose your preferred WSB council on the map

Direction

Click on ‘Get Directions’ to get routes to the preferred council from your location.

Tips for WSB volunteers

https://youtu.be/1xVXOPfwEiI

[interact id="5e9bee1cb789c100146c61c1" type="quiz"]


Who are we?

We are Tech Warriors with a Team of four Postgraduate students from Monash University. We are a peculiar bunch of very different people across the globe. One common belief we all share is to create a safer environment and make a difference in the community.
